success.question_text: What is the height of the window?

stimulus_1.text: A window is made up of a rectangle and a semi-circle.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

The radius of a circle is half the diameter.

success.question_text:
On 13 May, Simone found a bill that should have been paid on 27 April.

How many days overdue was the bill?

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Make sure you know how many days there are in every month.

success.question_text:
Turf is sold in 50 cm wide rolls that are, when unrolled, 3 m long. Felix wants to turf an area of his yard that is 8 m long and 6 m wide.

How many rolls of turf will he need?
What is the temperature shown on this thermometer?

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Take care when reading the scale on a graph or measuring device. Dividing the whole part by the number of divisions will give the amount of each division.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

‘kilo’ means thousand. 1 km = 1000 m, 1 kL = 1000 L, 1 kg = 1000 g, 1 kW = 1000 W and so on.

success.question_text:
An amount of money was shared in the ratio 3:5.

The smaller share was $60. What was the original amount of money?

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Order is very important in ratios.

success.question_text: How long is it from 3:40 pm Wednesday until 8:20 am Thursday?

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

From 3:40 pm until 4:20 pm is 40 minutes.

From 4:20 pm until 8:20 am the next day is 16 hours.

It is 16 hours and 40 minutes from 3:40 pm Wednesday until 8:20 am Thursday.

review_2.column_1_text:
Tip

Take care when calculating time differences. Remember time is not a decimal.

success.question_text:
A 5-litre bottle of water currently holds 2.4 litres. Justine uses 750 millilitres from the bottle and then completely refills it.

How many millilitres of water did Justine put into the bottle?

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

‘milli’ means thousandth. 1000 mL = 1 L, 1000 mm = 1 m, 1000 mg = 1 g and so on.

Tip

When adding or subtracting decimals, write them with the decimal points aligned and the same number of places after the decimal point.

success.question_text: What is the area of this rectangle?
How many minutes does Jennifer take to ride 8 kilometres at an average speed of 12 km/h?

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Think logically and you might find an easier way to answer a question. For example, in this question 8 is two-thirds of 12 so the time needed will be two-thirds of an hour.

success.question_text: What is the perimeter of this shape?

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

It is not always necessary to know the lengths of all the individual sides in order to find the perimeter.

success.question_text: What is the surface area of a cube with side length 8 cm?

stimulus_1.text: The diagram shows the top view of a swimming pool. It is filled to a constant depth of 1.5 metres.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

1 kilolitre is 1000 litres. One cubic metre will hold one kilolitre.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

The height of any prism or cylinder is not necessarily the vertical measurement. The height must be the perpendicular height, at right angles to the base.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

If a question asks for an estimate it is not necessary to work out the exact answer. If it is possible to find the exact answer, you may of course do so. For example, in this question the answer is 3.15 × 8 litres = 25.2 litres.
